This part of my life is called Happyness…. 
“And the Y, it’s an I there’s no Y in Happiness” 
- Pursuit Of Happiness

I listened something today and it confirmed what God had been putting on my heart- that I’m stepping into a new season, evolving if you will. 

Growth isn’t comfortable and I’m not gonna hold you the last few months I’ve been playing it safe. Some where between trying to find this balance between motherhood and the hustler I am, between trying to give myself grace but also  trying to get back to the old me that I knew no longer existed. I started playing it safe, doubting myself in fear I might disappoint myself. 

I say all that to say, earlier this week I told my manager I wasn’t going to participate in #Reelmas. Why? Because I didn’t want to commit to something I knew might not work out. Knowing all that’s on my plate and the ever changing schedule of a toddler,  I just knew it would be difficult to maintain the consistency.  BUT then the *Holy Spirit* reminded me I’m not only selling myself short but I’m saying saying that to God too. I mean He can and does do exceedingly and abundantly so who am I to say what I can’t do #1 without trying (Court you know better) #2 when He’s showed me time and time again that if I lean on Him, I have no reason to fear or doubt. 

Soooo you can officially count this as my entry into #itsReelsmas 🎞️🎄 keep me accountable ya’ll lol

Because homemade tomato soup is always a great idea 😋 
——

20 Roma tomatoes*
Olive oil
Minced Garlic 
Chopped onions 
Vegetable broth 
Italian 
Garlic powder 
Onion powder 
Salt 
Pepper
Salt 
Chil flakes if you like spice 
Grated Parmesan 
Spinach 

*if using canned roasted tomatoes skip to step 4 

1. Halve tomatoes, drizzle and season both sides with olive oil, Italian seasoning, salt, pepper. 

2. Place tomatoes it on the top rack of your oven on 450 degrees for 30 min. Flip them and roast for 10 more min

3. Remove charred skin but I left some on for the flavor 

4. In a large pot sauté until fragrant mined garlic and onions. I don’t measure but I used a medium yellow onion and about 4 -5 big cloves of garlic 

5. Once the onions are transparent add in about 2 cups of vegetable broth and season to taste with salt, pepper, garlic and onion powder, Italian seasoning, chili flakes and sugar. 

6. Add in tomatoes and simmer for 10 -15 minutes
 
7. Immersion blend or allow mixture to cool and blend in blender. Blend to your desired consistency. 

8. Taste and add any additional seasoning if desired 

9. Optional but I love adding in grated parm. It takes the taste and consistency to another level. 

10. Add in fresh spinach for a little healthy dazzle dazzle  and if you want extra greens some steamed broccoli 

Serve with bread sticks, crusty bread or grilled cheese 😋

Totally unplanned post today but I was probably a few moments away from crying Holy Spirit just reminded me to take a second. And did 

1 Peter 5:7 and Matthew 11:28-30

I have been so tired, overstimulated and stressed this week and it all pretty much came to a head. @capturedby_ty went of town for work this morning at 4am so not only was I tired from being up late because y’all niece did not want to go to bed lol and I had to wake up to take him to the airport. I’ve been walking around with a stress headache and tension in my back for the last and overall just been stressed and attempting to get it all done. 

And for my other mamas out there feeling the same, right on the brink. If you needed a reminder today to take a moment today, to ask for help, to push off the to do list until tomorrow, to rest in the Lord- here it is. 

I had so many plans for today and honestly if just may not get done but what did get done is some good ol, present quality time with my baby girl. Not me trying to work or think about what I had to do but just truly being present AND rest. I’m going to lay myself down with a heating pad and tens unit and relax. 

But He said to me, ‘My grace is sufficient for you, for my power is made perfect in weakness.’ Therefore I will boast all the more gladly about my weaknesses, so that Christ’s power may rest on me.” – 2 Corinthians 12:9

So, if you’re a mama-to-be or looking to help a girl friend or family member out, this is my must-have postpartum starter kit for most mamas all available on @Walmart (most because not every mama has the same journey). 

#WalmartPartner First up, the Frida Mom Postpartum Recovery Kit is a one-stop-shop for postpartum recovery. It comes with everything you need to take care of yourself down there, from disposable underwear to perineal cooling pads to a peri bottle. I also say to throw in an extra Frida Mom Upside Down Peri Bottle for a second bathroom or on the go. Trust me - it’s a game changer. 

When it comes to breastfeeding, a nursing pillow will save 👏🏽 your 👏🏽 back in the early stages. I recently came across the Frida Mom Nursing Pillow and it’s a yes for me because it’s designed to provide support and comfort for both you and baby.

Summer Essentials for the Littles! ☀️ #WalmartPartner I remember when summer rolled around I was looking for as many tips as I could about what would make summer time fun and easy, so I’m paying it forward. Here are some of my top tips and must-haves for parents with toddlers and babies, all available on @Walmart! 
 
Get a wagon! A stroller is amazing too but if last summer taught me anything a wagon definitely levels you up.  It’s more comfortable and can hold a lot more for the picnic and beach trips. It has great shade when the sun is beaming or that occasional chance of rain. We recently grabbed the Monbebe Wagon Stroller and Temple LOVES it. 
 
I always have a few extra items on hand for weather changes.  I love the outfits from Modern Moments that are lightweight. I’ll also keep a pair of pants and a sweater for cool nights. As well as a stroller fan to offer a nice breeze. 
 
Rash guard bathing suits and Pampers Splashers are a must. Whether we are at the sprinklers, backyard in the pool or at the beach, they keep babygirl all the way together. 
 
For sun protection we love the Think Baby SPF. It’s safe for her skin and effective. I also always have a sun hat on hand but with all her hair sometimes hats are out of the question lol. 
Last but not least snacks, snacks, snacks. I love something quick and nutritious like yummy Cerebelly bars and of course lots of fruit and water to keep her hydrated. 😎🌴 
 
Find all these amazing items and more linked in my stories on @Walmart! Drop some of your baby/toddler must haves for the summer! #Walmart #WelcomeToYourWalmart @collectivevoicehq

Once I stopped fighting this heat damage I found so much peace! 🫣 I’m very much at the point where I  considering become a straight natural but I do miss my curly hair some days 

You guys know that last year I ended up with heat damage after straightening my hair so much and not properly protecting it. I decided to grow it out instead of big chopping but y’all THE STRESS. 

At first, I resolved to not use any heat for a as long as it took to grow my hair out. Managing 3 different textures was a lot. The super thick, curly new growth at my roots, the silky straight texture in the middle, and random loose or curly/curly textures at the ends. A MESS

My wash days became longer, more stressful, I couldn’t figure out how to blend the textures without heat. 

Once I decided to lean into the heat damage (odd right) and started stretching my hair when it wasn’t in protective styles it gave me 

1. More flexibility
2. Shorter wash days
3. I can see my split ends and take care of them sooner than later 
4. Better length retention 

Have y’all been here before? Have you considered becoming a straight natural? 

#naturalhair #straightnatural #lengthretention #bycourtneydanielle #curlsandcouture
